{{Indian name|Lakshmibai|Venkatraman}}
'''Venkatraman Lakshmibai''' is an Indian mathematician who works as a professor of mathematics at [[Northeastern University]] in Boston. Her research concerns [[algebraic geometry]], the theory of [[algebraic group]]s, and [[representation theory]],{{r|profile}} including in particular the theory of [[Generalized flag variety|flag varieties]] and [[Schubert variety|Schubert varieties]].

Lakshmibai earned her PhD in 1976 from the [[Tata Institute of Fundamental Research]].{{r|profile}}
With [[Sara Billey]] she is the co-author of the monograph ''Singular Loci of Schubert Varieties'' (Progress in Mathematics 182, Birkhäuser, 2000).{{r|brion}}
She has also co-authored two monographs with Justin Brown: ''Flag Varieties: An Interplay of Geometry, Combinatorics, and Representation Theory'' (Texts and Readings in Mathematics 53, Hindustan Book Agency, 2009){{r|ohn}} and ''The Grassmannian Variety: Geometric and Representation-Theoretic Aspects'' (Developments in Mathematics 42, Springer, 2015).{{r|lili}}

In 2012 she was selected as one of the inaugural [[fellow]]s of the [[American Mathematical Society]].{{r|fams}}

