'''Friedrich Emil Fritz Prym''' (28 September 1841, [[Düren]] – 15 December 1915, [[Bonn]]) was a German [[mathematician]] who introduced [[Prym varieties]] and [[Prym differential]]s.

Prym completed his [[Ph.D.]] at the [[Humboldt University of Berlin|University of Berlin]] in 1863 with a thesis written under the direction of [[Ernst Kummer]] and [[Martin Ohm]].  In 1867 he started a Professor at the [[University of Würzburg]], where he later became Dean, and then [[Rector (academia)|Rector]] in 1897–98.

