'''Kenji Ueno''' (上野 健爾, Ueno Kenji, 1945, [[Kumamoto Prefecture]]) is a Japanese mathematician, specializing in [[algebraic geometry]].<ref name="HomepageRef">[http://researchmap.jp/kenjiueno/?lang=english Ueno's homepage]</ref>

He was in the 1970s at the [[University of Tokyo]] and was from 1987 to 2009 a professor at the [[University of Kyoto]] and is now the director of [[Yokkaichi University]]'s [[Seki Kōwa]] Institute for Mathematics.<ref name=HomepageRef/> In 1978 he was an Invited Speaker (''Classification of algebraic manifolds'') at the [[International Congress of Mathematicians]] in [[Helsinki]].<ref>{{cite book|editor=Lehto, Olli|editorlink=Olli Lehto|title=Proceedings of the International Congress of Mathematicians, 1978|year=1980|location=Helsinki|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=eQC7AAAAIAAJ|isbn=9789514103520}}</ref>

Ueno was a visiting professor at several universities, including the [[University of Bonn]] and the [[University of Mannheim]] in the 1970s.

He is the author and editor of several books on algebraic geometry.<ref>[http://researchmap.jp/kenjiueno/ Biographical information]</ref>

